<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="30" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Commercial Agreement/32:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-21T17:00:00-04:00">September 21, 1934—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>97. Your 259, September 21, 5 p.m. The Agreement was signed on behalf of
                            United States September 20. Every effort will be made to obtain
                            favorable action by Senate promptly after next session starts.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>